Instruction.1: Take a roughly shoulder width grip. There should be a straight line from your elbow to fist (vertical forearms).
Instruction.2: Pull your chin back and press the weight toward the ceiling by extending at the elbow joint and flexing at the shoulder joint.
Instruction.3: Press until your elbows are extended and push your head forward slightly.
Instruction.4: Return to the start position with control. Pulling your chin back to allow the bar to pass your face safely.

Instruction.1: Take a double overhand roughly shoulder width grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight up the ceiling. Aim to get the bar to chin level or slightly higher.

Instruction.1: Begin by sitting on the ground with your legs extended and a barbell in your hands, with your palms facing forward and your elbows bent.
Instruction.2: Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, lift the barbell up from your chest and press it straight up above your head.
Instruction.3: Lower the barbell back down to your chest.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine leaning forward slightly with the end of the barbell held in one hand at your shoulder with your elbow positioned beneath your wrist.
Instruction.2: While keeping your elbow pointed forward, drive the bar directly overhead, switching hands at the top of the movement. Lower the bar back down to the other side of your body, mirroring the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for desired number of reps, switching hands at the top of each rep.

WorkoutName: Landmine Half Kneeling Single Arm Overhead Press

Instruction.1: Start by lying flat on your back with your legs extended towards the landmine attachment and your arms overhead, holding the landmine barbell with both hands while engaging your core muscles by pressing your lower back into the ground and drawing your belly button in towards your spine.
Instruction.2: Lift your legs off the ground, keeping them together and straight, and simultaneously raise your upper body off the ground, reaching the landmine barbell away from your face.
Instruction.3: Hold this position for the desired duration, then carefully lower the barbell to the ground.

Instruction.1: Start in a kneeling position facing the barbell with one hand holding the end of the barbell at your shoulder with your elbow tucked beneath your wrist.
Instruction.2: Keeping your elbow pointing forward, drive the barbell up overhead until your arm is fully extended and switch the bar to your other hand at the top of the movement.
Instruction.3: Control the descent of the bar to your other shoulder and repeat movement for desired reps, switching hands at the top of each rep.

Instruction.1: Start kneeling in front of the landmine, facing towards it, with your knees hip-width apart and your back straight while holding the end of the bar in both hands in front of your chest.
Instruction.2: Push the landmine up overhead by fully extending your arms until the weight is directly over your head. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the landmine back down to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand perpendicularly to the barbell, holding the end of the bar at your outer hip with your inner hand and your palm facing your body.
Instruction.2: While keeping your core braced and your arm straight, lift the barbell diagonally up and towards the direction of the landmine attachment, then return the bar to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine attachment while holding the end of the bar with one hand at your shoulder on the same side with your elbow tucked to your body underneath your wrist.
Instruction.2: Step back with the leg on the same side that you are holding the bar on and with control lower yourself down into a lunge position while keeping your core engaged and torso tall, then drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Once your feet are back in the starting position, drive the bar up overhead until your arm is fully extended, then lower the bar back down to the starting position.
Instruction.4: Repeated for the desired number of reps, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the landmine, holding the end of the bar in both hands with your palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: Extend your arms upward, pressing the end of the bar up overhead. Pause at the top of the movement, then lower the bar with control back to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Stand perpendicularly to the barbell with the end of the bar in front of your feet. Squat down and hold the end of the bar with your hand closer to the landmine attachment with your palm facing your body.
Instruction.2: Drive your feet into the ground to start the motion. As your legs fully extend, pull the bar upwards with your hand and start to rotate your torso in towards the landmine attachment. As you do so, bring your other hand up to the bar and switch your grip. Press through the bar to extend your arm all the way upright, pivoting your back foot to allow for more trunk rotation.
Instruction.3: Perform the movement in reverse to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start sitting on the ground facing the landmine attachment with your legs open for stability while holding the end of the bar in a neutral grip with your hand resting at your shoulder and your elbow beneath your wrist.
Instruction.2: Leaning forward slightly, press the bar up into the air until your arm is fully extended. At the top of the movement, switch which hand is holding the end of the bar and lower the bar back down to the opposite shoulder. Perform again to return the bar to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground facing the landmine with your legs spread. Hold the end of the bar in both hands in front of your chest with your palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: While keeping your torso tall and core brace, drive the end of the bar upward until your arms are fully extended. Lean forward slightly for full range of motion in the shoulder joints. Lower the bar back down to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Repeat for desired number of reps.

WorkoutName: Landmine Seated Single Arm Overhead Press

Instruction.1: Sit on the ground facing the landmine with your legs spread. Hold the end of the bar in one hand in front of that shoulder with your palm facing across your body.
Instruction.2: While keeping your torso tall and your core braced, drive the bar upwards until your arm is fully extended, leaning forward slightly for full range of motion in the shoulder joint. Lower the bar back down to the starting position with control.
Instruction.3: Repeat for desired number of reps on one side, then switch sides.

Instruction.1: Stand in front of the landmine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, palm facing in, and bring it to shoulder height with your elbow tucked beneath your hand.
Instruction.2: Dip your body slightly then drive up through the ground to generate momentum as your extend your arm fully upwards. Pause briefly at the top of the rep, then lower the weight back down to the starting position with control.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps on one side before switching sides.

WorkoutName: Landmine Single Arm Staggered Overhead Press

Instruction.1: Stand facing the bar in a split stance with one leg forward and bent and the other back and straight. Hold the bar in the hand on the side of the leg that is back with the end of the bar at your shoulder with your elbow tucked beneath your hand.
Instruction.2: Drive the bar upwards until your arm is fully extended. Pause briefly before lowering the end of the bar back down to the starting position with control.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Hold the end of the bar in front of you.
Instruction.2: Pop your hips, pull your elbows up to the ceiling, and get underneath the bar.

Instruction.1: Hold the bar with a goblet position.
Instruction.2: Push your hips back and sink into a squat.
Instruction.3: Push through your heels and squat back up. Use the momentum you generate at the legs to push the bar over head.
Instruction.4: Let the bar return to the goblet position before starting the next rep.

WorkoutName: Barbell Behind The Neck Seated Overhead Press

Instruction.1: Take a roughly shoulder width grip. There should be a straight line from your elbow to fist (vertical forearms).
Instruction.2: Push your head foward and press the weight toward the ceiling by extending at the elbow joint and flexing at the shoulder joint.
Instruction.3: Press until your elbows are extended and push your head forward slightly.

Instruction.1: Hold a barbell at shoulder height with a pronated grip.
Instruction.2: Press the barbell over your head.
Instruction.3: Lower it behind your head, then return to the front. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on an incline bench with an overhand grip on the barbell. Raise your arms until your fists are pointed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Return to the start under control. This exercise is prone to using momentum when you begin to fatigue.

Instruction.1: Position the bench between 30 and 45 degrees.
Instruction.2: Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower the bar to your mid chest
Instruction.4: Raise the bar (slowly and controlled) until you've locked your elbows.

Instruction.1: Position the bench between 45 and 60 degrees.
Instruction.2: Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower the bar to your mid chest
Instruction.4: Raise the bar (slowly and controlled) until you've locked your elbows.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the bar just outside your knees. Pull the bar from the floor by driving through your legs, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: As the bar reaches your hips, extend explosively, shrug, and drop under to catch it in a front squat position with elbows high. Stand up tall.
Instruction.3: Dip slightly, then drive through your legs to push the bar overhead.
Instruction.4: Stabilize the bar overhead, lock arms, then bring feet together before lowering the bar safely.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip the barbell with a wide overhand grip, and keep your back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.2: Lift the barbell by explosively extending your hips, knees, and ankles while keeping the bar close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches chest level, rotate your wrists and elbows up and back, transitioning into an overhead press.
Instruction.4: Fully extend your arms overhead, stabilize the bar, then lower it back to the starting position with control.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide (outside shoulders), hook grip recommended.
Instruction.2: Keep chest up, back straight, and drive through heels to lift the bar off the ground, keeping it close to your body.
Instruction.3: As the bar reaches mid-thigh, explode upwards by extending hips, knees, and ankles, shrugging shoulders and pulling the bar high.
Instruction.4: Drop under the bar slightly, catching it overhead with arms locked out. Stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, barbell over midfoot. Grip the bar wide with an overhand grip, chest up, and back straight.
Instruction.2: Lift the bar by driving through your legs, keeping it close to your body. Extend your hips and knees while maintaining a straight back.
Instruction.3: Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles while shrugging your shoulders. Pull yourself under the bar as it moves upward.
Instruction.4: Drop into a deep squat while locking the bar overhead. Stabilize, then stand up fully to complete the lift.

Instruction.1: Start with the barbell on your shoulders in a front rack position, feet hip-width apart. Slightly bend your knees and dip straight down.
Instruction.2: Explosively extend your legs and push the barbell upward, generating momentum with your legs.
Instruction.3: As the bar rises, quickly split your legs (one forward, one back) and drop under the bar, locking your arms overhead.
Instruction.4: Bring your front foot back, then your back foot forward to a stable standing position with the bar locked overhead.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine, feet flat, and grab the handles with palms facing down, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: Pull handles towards your lower abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking elbows. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Press your chest into the chest pad and grab the horizontal handles with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles toward you, make sure your elbows stay flared out.

Instruction.1: Place your chest against the pad and grab the handles with an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight back and keep your elbows flared throughout the rep.

Instruction.1: Sit on machine and press your chest into the pad.
Instruction.2: Grab the handles with an overhand grip. Keep your elbows mostly extended.
Instruction.3: Bring your arms backwards and squeeze your scapula together.

Instruction.1: Adjust the seat to match your height.
Instruction.2: Press your back into the back pad.
Instruction.3: Press upwards until your elbows are nearly extended. But not fully extended.
Instruction.4: Lower until the plates nearly touch back down.

Instruction.1: Adjust the seat to match your height.
Instruction.2: Press your back into the back pad.
Instruction.3: Press upwards until your elbows are nearly extended. But not fully extended.
Instruction.4: Lower until the plates nearly touch back down.

WorkoutName: Machine Plate Loaded Front Military Press

Instruction.1: Grab the two handles and raise the arms straight out to your sides.
Place the top of your hand into the small of your back, your arm at a 90 degree angle.
Instruction.2: Hold your elbow with the other arm, and slowly pull the arm forward until you feel your shoulder engaged in the stretch. Pause at the apex of the stretch and return to the starting position.
Instruction.3: Return to starting position, and repeat with your other arm.

Instruction.1: Start with your arms at either side. Begin by pushing your shoulders forward and in towards your chest.
Instruction.2: Continue the circular motion with your shoulders, pinching up towards your ears, and then extending your chest outwards while you finish the motion.
Instruction.3: Repeat as necessary.

Instruction.1: Reach one arm behind your body, with your elbow pointing upward behind your head.
Instruction.2: Assist the stretch with your other hand on your elbow to engage your shoulder.
Instruction.3: Pause for a few seconds, then repeat the stretch with your other arm.

Instruction.1: Start with the pole in front of you with an overhand wider than shoulder width grip.
Instruction.2: Rotate one arm overhead and behind while keeping the other arm in front of you.
Instruction.3: Then rotate the other arm.
Instruction.4: Bring the original arm back to the starting position, then the other arm. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Inhale and brace your abdominals
Instruction.2: Raise the arms vertically while keeping the elbows slightly bent
Instruction.3: Once the arms are parallel with the floor, rotate the plate clockwise and counterclockwise.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate held in front of your face with both hands, palms facing each other.
Instruction.2: Rotate the plate around the head, keeping the arms extended and moving the plate in a circular motion.
Instruction.3: Complete one full circle, then reverse the direction to complete another circle.

Instruction.1: Stand tall holding two plates at your side.
Instruction.2: Lateral raise the plates to your side and continue until the plates are pointed at the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Let your shoulder joint naturally rotate. At the bottom you should have a neutral or overhand grip. By the time the plates are overhead, your palms should be facing forward.

WorkoutName: Plate Internally Rotated Rear Delt Fly

Instruction.1: With plates in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Hinge forward with a flat back.
Instruction.2: Maintain an overhand grip and internally rotated shoulders.
Instruction.3: Raise your arms backward toward the ceiling while maintaining a light band in your elbows.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and grip two plates in each hand at your sides.
Instruction.2: Keeping your arms straight, raise the plates out to your sides until they are in line with your shoulders.
Instruction.3: Lower the plates back to your sides with control. Repeat for desired number of reps.

Instruction.1: Keep your back straight and bend forward slightly at the waist.
Instruction.2: With arms extended, raise the weights out to your sides until they are in line with your shoulders.
Instruction.3: Pause briefly and then lower the weights back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Start in a standing position with a plate against your chest.
Instruction.2: Press the plate away from your body until your elbows are extended.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the feet.
Instruction.2: Bend the knees and hips to pick up the plate, keeping the back straight and core engaged.
Instruction.3: Stand up, lock the hips and legs, and press the plate overhead with straight arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back to the starting position, keeping control of it, and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the torso, palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Curl the plate up to the front of the shoulder while keeping the elbows close to the body.
Instruction.3: Rotate the palms to face forward and press the plate overhead, locking out the arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back to the starting position, keeping control of it, and repeat for desired reps.

WorkoutName: Plate Curl To Overhead Press To Tricep Extension

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the torso, palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Curl the plate up to the front of the shoulder while keeping the elbows close to the body.
Instruction.3: Rotate the palms to face forward and press the plate overhead, locking out the arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back behind the head to the starting position of a tricep extension.
Instruction.5: Push the plate back up overhead, then lower it back to the starting position and repeat for desired reps.

WorkoutName: Plate Overhead Press To Tricep Extension

Instruction.1: Brace your core and press the weight plate overhead until your arms are fully extended. Keep your shoulders down and back.
Instruction.2: While your arms are fully extended, lower the weight behind your head to perform the extension
Instruction.3: After completing the extension, lower the weight to your chest, and perform the overhead press. Repeat

Instruction.1: Start by standing upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a single weight plate overhead with both hands, keeping your arms extended straight above your head.
Instruction.2: Begin walking forward, taking slow and steady steps while maintaining a straight line. Your focus should be on maintaining balance and control of the weight plate overhead.
Instruction.3: As you walk, continue to keep your arms extended and the weight plate overhead. Try to maintain good posture and avoid leaning forward or backward, as this could result in losing control of the weight plate.
Instruction.4: Continue walking for a set distance or for a certain amount of time, keeping your focus on proper form and technique. When finished, return to the starting position and repeat as desired.

Instruction.1: Start with the plate at chest height. Begin a squat.
Instruction.2: Make sure to hit parallel depth. On your way back up, use the momentum you generate with your legs to help push the plate into an overhead position.
Instruction.3: Let the plate return to chest height before initiating the next squat.

Instruction.1: Place feet on Bosu, hips high, hands on the floor.
Instruction.2: Lower the head towards the ground, then push back up.
Instruction.3: Keep legs straight and hips elevated throughout.

Instruction.1: Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar.
Instruction.2: Lower the bar to your mid chest
Instruction.3: Raise the bar until you've locked your elbows.

Instruction.1: Position the bench between 30 and 45 degrees.
Instruction.2: Lay flat on the bench with your feet on the ground. With straight arms unrack the bar.
Instruction.3: Lower the bar to your mid chest
Instruction.4: Raise the bar (slowly and controlled) until you've locked your elbows.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with dumbbells at either side, palms facing your hips.
Instruction.2: Raise your arms on either side with a slight bend in your elbow until they are parallel with the floor. Pause at the top of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly return your arms down to starting position.

Instruction.1: With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.
Instruction.2: With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Sit on a bench with back support. Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height with your palms forward.
Instruction.2: Raise the dumbbells upwards and pause at the contracted position.
Instruction.3: Lower the weights back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Grab two dumbbells while standing upright with the dumbbells at your side.
Instruction.2: Raise the two dumbbells with your elbows being fully extended until the dumbbells are eye level.
Instruction.3: Lower the weights in a controlled manner to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: With dumbbells in either hand, bend your knees with your feet slightly bowed out. Arch your back above your knees, and start with the weights touching in front of your chest.
Instruction.2: With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Hinge forward at the hips while maintaining a flat back. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench and let your arms freely.
Instruction.2: Lateral raise your arms straight out to the side until your arms are about parallel with the ground.

Instruction.1: With dumbbells in either hand, lay on an incline bench that's at about 15-30 degrees.
Instruction.2: With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Laying Reverse Fly Internally Rotated

Instruction.1: With dumbbells in either hand and an overhand grip, lay on an incline bench that is roughly 15 - 30 degrees high.
Instruction.2: With bent elbows, raise your arms up to shoulder level, pausing at the at the end of the motion.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower your arms back to starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin seated on an upright bench with your palms facing you.
Instruction.2: Begin pressing toward the ceiling. As you press, rotate your palms.
Instruction.3: As you extend your elbows fully your palms should be facing forward.
